g.text: You: "I think I know that woman."
You: "I'm not going to answer that, lieutenant."
Authority: He's not leaving you a lot of room to back off from this.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Mhm," he nods. "What else did you do?"
You: "I asked her where we are, what city is this, maybe even *what year*. Something like that."
You: "She knows I did some pretty crazy stuff before I passed out. That I partied hard. And not very mental-healthily."
Inland Empire: So this is what it feels like to be *interviewed*...
Horrific Necktie: You'll get through it, you slippery fuck! Blast some insane-o at him, throw him off.
Rhetoric: Is it, though? 'Nothing'? You're still in for a bumpy ride here, try not to mess it up.
You: "Better not to add anything to that."
Kim Kitsuragi: He repeats: "Officer, before we interview this woman -- is there something I should know?"
Horrific Necktie: Of course it is, you slippery fuck! Blast some insane-o at him, throw him off.
Rhetoric: Whatever you do, don't say the first thing.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm going to assume she overheard you -- anything else?"
You: "I met her. In the hallway, after I woke up."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's not nothing, you were coming apart at the seams." He looks you in the eye: "Do you know the assault victim?"
You: "She overheard me listening to music and doing weird things. From her room. It's the one next to yours."
Kim Kitsuragi: He shrugs. "That's clearly your interrogation technique. Anything else?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Is there something I should know before we talk to her?"
Inland Empire: You'll get through it.
Jump to: [You: ""I think I know that woman.""]
Esprit de Corps: His opinion of you has lowered considerably.
You: "I tried to hit on her..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "The victim? Is there something I should know before we talk to her?"
Half Light: Ice is forming on the inside of your chest cavity, cold sweat trickles down your neck...
Kim Kitsuragi: "It *is*," he nods. "This would have been good to know *before*."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Wonderful. I'm going to assume she overheard you -- anything else?"
Esprit de Corps: You feel fortified by his assurance. It's going to be all right.
You: "She knows I didn't remember being a cop."
You: "She said I'm going to have to interrogate her later and it's going to *suck* for me."
You: "And the... sort of... quivering jello thing with the eye?" (Point to your twitching eye.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "Then don't *ever* say that again." There's a pause.
You: "It's an art thing. You wouldn't understand."
You: "It went pretty okay, I guess."
You: "You mean the sweating and the fidgeting when he mentioned her name?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "You looked strange when he mentioned the assault victim's name." He looks you in the eye: "Do you know that woman?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "So she overheard you? Or did you *party* together?"
You: I got nothing to hide.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It doesn't matter how it *went* officer -- what else?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "What you're saying is..." he says in a low, calm voice. "*You* raped her?"
Inland Empire: I wouldn't say it is.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Understood -- you were not in good shape on Monday."
Kim Kitsuragi: "This is unprofessional." He repeats: "Not sharing information with me is *unprofessional*."
Inland Empire: What if you do -- but you just don't *remember* that you do?
You: "Yeah, we partied all right. Partied all night like the Inzany Boys."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It should have. Anything else?"
Kim Kitsuragi: He nods. "We'll be all right, officer. This is nothing."
"We'll be all right, lieutenant. This is nothing."
